{center}
{subhead}CrossFire II Game Released{def}
{left}
{pp}
A new shoot 'em up game has been released by APC&TCP for the Amiga.
You play a rebel pilot called Karsten, who has to escort or defend
your people from attack from others in a series of missions.
{pp}
Features:
{pp}
* atmospheric story{p}
* rendered graphics and animation {p}
* atmospheric music for each situation {p}
* 40 different weapons{p}
* 3 game modes{p}
* Campaign (single player) missions{p}
* Dogfight (upto 4 players){p}
* Survival-Modus (4 players vs computer){p}
* Versions for AGA and Graphics boards
{pp}
Requirements:
{p}
* AmigaOS 3.1 (also Amithlon, Winuae and Morphos){p}
* 16/32Mb Memory{p}
* 68030 or PPC{p}
* AGA/Graphics Card{p}
* 50MB Hard disk space{p}
* CDROM
{pp}